<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>“Mam’ Winnie’s suffering should not be forgotten. “We need to keep remembering the sacrifices she made for the people of this country. “Winnie inspired me, especially with her bravery in fighting the apartheid regime.” Msindisi runs Hand in Hand Visual Art Studio with his older brother, Sakhimuzi.He said he would ask the municipality to rename the park to honour the late struggle hero. “This will help to teach young people about Winnie’s struggle against apartheid.” “Most youngsters don’t know anything about apartheid and what contribution Winnie made during those dark years. “The only thing they know is that Winnie was the ex-wife of Nelson Mandela.”Mthubanzi Mniki, a spokesman for Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality, advised Msindisi to approach the municipality with his proposal. “He should go to the department of arts and culture in St George’s Park. In terms of changing or renaming municipal buildings, roads or infrastructure, a person has to get approval from the department,” he said.